$interpreted: Stewart: ...The prohibited Panther territory, untouched for hundreds of years. Due to the lack of development, this place is still rich with Soul Energy.
Stewart: Haha, what a pristine location! I can already smell the money it's gonna make me!
Jerus: Indeed. None of the other Panthers were able to realize the value of this place.
Jerus: Our ancestors said no entry and those morons blindly obeyed for hundreds of years. Look at all these resources here, what a waste.
Stewart: This place is located deep within Panther territory. On top of that, Charle has also forbidden anyone from entering here.
Stewart: If not for those reasons, we would've developed this place a long time ago.
Jerus: All we need to do now is get rid of Fatima and those stubborn traditionalists. As with the other members, it won't be too hard to persuade them.
Jerus: You can rest assured.
Stewart: Last time, even though you dropped me a hint about Fatima's patrol schedule and I unleashed the beasts to assault her, it still failed.
Stewart: Will it go smoothly this time?
Jerus: No need to worry. The two sides are probably at each other's throats by now.
Jerus: I snuck one of my men into Fatima's crew. I've ordered him to kill Fatima and Charle amid the chaos if the chance presents itself.
Stewart: With those two dead and your cooperation, no one will be able to stop me from taking full advantage of this place! Muhahaha~
Fatima: Jerus! So it really was you who sold out everyone!
Jerus: W-Why are you here?
Fatima: The subordinate you snuck into my crew has been busted. He confessed everything!
Jerus: That worthless piece of...damnit...
Fatima: How dare you sell out the land our ancestors left us just so you can live an easier life?
Fatima: Do you have any idea what you are doing!?
Jerus: All I desire is to live a life like the people in the outside world. I'm sick and tired of night patrols, hunting, and being restrained by ancient rules!
Jerus: As long as I get to leave behind this kind of mundane life, I am willing to do anything!
Fatima: By allowing outsiders into Panther territory, you are destroying the Panthers' traditional lifestyle that has been passed down for generations.
Fatima: In the future, our children may no longer be allowed to run around freely in Whistlewood Valley. Have you ever thought about that!?
Jerus: I don't want to hear your crap! You had this coming a long time ago. Boys, get 'er! I don't care if you kill her!
Charle: Excuse me, if you're talking to your subordinates who were hiding nearby, I just took care of them all.
Tica: I also helped take down one or two of them!
Tica: Eh...or was it five? Maybe six, I think?
Jerus: H, how is that possible...
Stewart: ......!?
Fatima: Charle, Jerus has betrayed the Panthers. I shall punish him myself. You stay out of this!
Fatima: Jerus, it's time to finish our business!
Jerus: FATIMA!
Fatima: Jerus' crimes will be judged by the Panthers. I don't want outsiders to be a part of this. Got a problem with that?
Charle: Not at all. As for that merchant...
Charle: I will let the Commerce Chamber determine his punishment.
Stewart: .........
Tica: Just now, I saw him fall into this big hole...
Tica: Therefore, I took advantage of the opportunity and arrested him~
Fatima: By the way, about Jerus' collusion with outsiders and their attempt to develop the prohibited territory, you knew about that all this time?
Charle: I had heard of it, but I was uncertain who the culprit was. That's why Tica and I decided to investigate the suspects in private.
Fatima: So all that stuff about you getting lost in the forest, that was just you trying to sound me out?
Charle: After our initial meeting, I decided that you're someone worth trusting. I was going to tell you everything I knew about the case.
Charle: Unfortunately, the situation got out of hand way too fast. I had no choice but to fake my defeat in order to lure out the mastermind once and for all.
Fatima: No wonder. I knew you weren't that weak...
Fatima: But why would an outsider like you care so much about the Panthers' prohibited territory? Could it be...that you're trying to have it all for yourself!?
Charle: You've got me all wrong. The prohibited territory is the water source and habitat for the animals.

Charle: 
If this place is developed, not only will it destroy the ecological balance of Whistlewood Valley, but it'll also affect the hunting lifestyle of the Panthers.
Fatima: For real? If that's the case, our ancestors prohibited us from stepping foot on this land because...
Charle: They want future Panther kin to not disturb the animals. Even though they are prey, they still need a place to reproduce and raise their younglings.
Charle: The prohibition was all to preserve the prosperity of Whistlewood Valley.
Charle: Also, since the Rune Academy studies Soul Energy, moving out of Whistlewood Valley is really not a viable option for us.
Charle: Even though I have already ordered students to only take a minimal amount of Soul Energy, it still has had a negative impact on the Panthers...
Fatima: Then what do you want?
Charle: I sincerely invite the Panthers to sit down and have a proper discussion about this.
Charle: Together, we'll figure out a method that won't interfere with the Panthers' cultural lifestyles and will allow us to continue our research. Is that fair?
Fatima: ...As long as you agree to give Panthers the utmost respect, I can convince my comrades to have a discussion with the Academy.
Fatima: However, I cannot guarantee that everyone will be willing to trust you.
Tica: Come on~ We've already compromised a lot. Why can't we just wrap this up already?
Charle: Tica! Watch your mouth!
Charle: Apologies, Tica has no ill intentions. Please forgive her.
Fatima: Whatever. I will forward your message. You should leave here soon. As for the remaining details, the Panthers shall await your future notice.
Charle: Understood. Tica, secure that bad guy. We need to go now.
Charle: Farewell, Fatima of the Panthers.
Fatima: Hmph, same old trick, up until the very end...
Fatima: ... Farewell, Charle of the Rune Academy.
Fatima: Looks like there are still humans who we can communicate with properly.
